  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel au Coeur du Village is a contemporary five star luxury hotel situated in the charming resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9}" title="La Clusaz">La Clusaz</a>. Everything has been thought out to provide guests with the best experience, the staff aim to provide all guests with a personalised experience - so you will want to return year after year. </p>
<h2>Excellent location</h2>
<p>The hotel has an excellent location in resort with direct access to the ski lifts and ski school meeting point, you can even ski back to the hotel at the end of the day.  The rustic resort centre is just a short walk away from the hotel, offering a range of shops, bars and restaurants serving delicious Savoyard cuisine. </p>
<h2>Restaurants and bars</h2>
<p>Start the day off with a delicious continental breakfast buffet before heading out onto the mountain and return to an appetizing three course evening meal, which is often a <span>contemporary take on the traditional cuisine. The bar is also open for lunch and afternoon tea, so if you are having a break from skiing you can enjoy a variety of snacks and light meals. </span>After a long day skiing, relax in the hotel's lounge area with fire place with a cocktail or glass of wine, it is the perfect place to unwind.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>Guests have fully use of the swimming pool and wellness area. Access to children is restricted to specific hours, so it is a tranquil experience for the older guests. Soothe your aches and pains in the relaxation pool with current jets, swan neck fountains, and hydro jets . The rock crystal steam room with a starlit ceiling and the wooden sauna with chromotherapy lights complete the spa circuit. There is also a sun deck where you can kick back and watch the world go by from the wide bay windows which face out onto the the snowy peaks. Massages and treatments are also available for a local fee, allowing you to completely rest and decompress.</p>
<p>The rooms are stylishly decorated with lavish extras, including fur rugs and mountain décor.  The suites also include a living room and all have a balcony with picturesque views of the village and the slopes, so you can marvel at your surroundings from the comfort of your room.</p>
