  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Junior Rooms</strong> are around 20m² and sleep one to two people with a queen-sized bed and have an en-suite bathroom with multi-jet shower and separate WC.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege Rooms</strong> are around 25m², sleeping two people with a king sized bed and have a bathtub with shower attachment in the bathroom. These rooms also benefit from having a cosy snug area or a balcony with views of the surrounding mountains.</p>
<p><strong>Privilege Suites</strong> sleep two to four people and are around 48m². The suites are made up as a double room with a king size bed with a separate en-suite bathroom and a balcony overlooking the resort and/or surrounding mountains. The second area is a spacious lounge area which can be made up as a single bed or a guest bed, suitable for one adult or two children under 12 years and also has a separate bathroom with a shower. </p>
<p><strong>Family Suites</strong> sleep three to four people and are around 60m². These suites are made up of two double bedrooms with a king size bed and have an en-suite featuring a bath or walk shower, these rooms also have a balcony. Can be duplex. The Family Suite is on request, please give our reservations team a call to book this room type.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
